## 3. Training Pipeline & Data Strategy

### 3.1 Multi-Stage Training Pipeline

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Stage 1: Foundation (3 months)"
        A[Code Corpus Collection<br/>2T tokens] --> B[Deduplication & Cleaning]
        B --> C[Quality Scoring]
        C --> D[Pre-Training<br/>Next-Token Prediction]
    end
    
    subgraph "Stage 2: Code Mastery (2 months)"
        D --> E[Language-Specific Fine-Tuning<br/>All 50+ Languages]
        E --> F[Framework-Specific Training<br/>React, Django, Spring, etc.]
        F --> G[Architecture Pattern Training<br/>Microservices, Monoliths, etc.]
    end
    
    subgraph "Stage 3: Enterprise Alignment (1 month)"
        G --> H[RLHF with Expert Engineers]
        H --> I[Security-Aware Alignment]
        I --> J[Compliance Rule Injection]
        J --> K[Code Quality Optimization]
    end
    
    subgraph "Stage 4: Agentic Capability (1 month)"
        K --> L[Tool Use Training<br/>Git, Docker, CI/CD, Debuggers]
        L --> M[Multi-Step Reasoning]
        M --> N[Self-Correction Training]
        N --> O[Final Evaluation]
    end
```

### 3.2 Training Data Strategy

> [!CAUTION]
> Data quality is the #1 determinant of model quality. Every competitor's weakness traces back to training data gaps.

#### Data Sources & Curation

| Source | Volume | Purpose | Quality Control |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Curated OSS Repositories** | 800B tokens | Language/framework diversity | Star count > 100, test coverage > 60%, active maintenance |
| **Enterprise Code (Partnered)** | 400B tokens | Real-world enterprise patterns | NDA-protected, anonymized, style-diverse across MNCs |
| **Technical Documentation** | 200B tokens | API knowledge, best practices | Official docs only, version-tagged |
| **Security Corpus** | 100B tokens | Vulnerability patterns & fixes | CVE database, OWASP, security research papers |
| **Architecture Case Studies** | 50B tokens | System design patterns | Curated from published architecture reviews |
| **Test Suites** | 200B tokens | Test-writing capability | Projects with >80% coverage, well-structured tests |
| **Code Reviews** | 150B tokens | Quality reasoning | High-quality review discussions from top OSS projects |
| **Synthetic Agentic Data** | 100B tokens | Multi-step task execution | Self-generated → human-verified agentic traces |

#### Data Quality Pipeline

```
Raw Code → License Filter → Dedup (MinHash) → Quality Score (AST parse, lint, test pass) 
  → Security Scan (no embedded secrets) → PII Removal → Provenance Tag → Final Corpus
```

### 3.3 Model Architecture Specifications

| Parameter | Saturday Lightning | Saturday Standard | Saturday Deep |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Parameters** | 3B | 70B | 405B |
| **Architecture** | Decoder-only Transformer | Decoder-only Transformer | MoE Transformer (128 experts, 8 active) |
| **Context Window** | 32K tokens | 256K tokens | 1M tokens |
| **Positional Encoding** | RoPE | RoPE with YaRN extension | RoPE with YaRN + sliding window |
| **Attention** | Grouped-Query Attention | GQA + Flash Attention 3 | GQA + Ring Attention for 1M context |
| **Normalization** | RMSNorm | RMSNorm | RMSNorm |
| **KV Cache** | Standard | Paged KV-Cache | Paged + Hierarchical KV-Cache |
| **Special Modules** | — | Code Graph Adapter | Code Graph Adapter + Reasoning Chain Module |
| **Training Compute** | 500 H100-hours | 50K H100-hours | 500K H100-hours |

