## 5. Security & Compliance Layer

### 5.1 Zero-Trust Code Generation Model

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Saturday Generates Code] --> B[Layer 1: Syntax & Logic Validation]
    B --> C[Layer 2: SAST - Static Security Scan]
    C --> D[Layer 3: Dependency CVE Check]
    D --> E[Layer 4: Compliance Policy Engine]
    E --> F[Layer 5: IP/License Scan]
    F --> G[Layer 6: Secrets Detection]
    G --> H{All 6 Layers Pass?}
    H -->|No| I[Auto-Remediate + Re-Scan]
    I --> B
    H -->|Yes| J[✅ Code Delivered with<br/>Security Certificate]
```

### 5.2 Compliance Framework Support

| Framework | Support Level | What Saturday Does |
|---|---|---|
| **SOC 2 Type II** | Full | Generates audit-ready code; enforces access controls; maintains audit trails |
| **GDPR** | Full | PII detection in code; data handling pattern enforcement; right-to-deletion patterns |
| **HIPAA** | Full | PHI handling rules; encryption enforcement; minimum necessary access patterns |
| **PCI-DSS** | Full | Cardholder data protection patterns; secure coding standards enforcement |
| **ISO 27001** | Full | Information security controls in generated code; risk-based approach |
| **EU AI Act** | Full | Transparency tags; human oversight hooks; risk classification support |
| **NIST AI RMF** | Full | AI risk management patterns; bias detection; fairness validation |
| **FedRAMP** | Partial | Federal security control alignment; FIPS-compliant crypto suggestions |

