### 6.1 Target Benchmarks

| Benchmark | Current Best (Feb 2026) | Saturday Target | How |
|---|---|---|---|
| **SWE-bench Verified** | Claude Opus 4.6: 79.2% | **>85%** | HCGE + deep reasoning chain + agentic self-repair |
| **SWE-rebench** | Claude Code + Opus 4.6: 52.9% | **>60%** | Novel problem training data + exploration reward |
| **SWE-bench Pro** | GPT-5: 23.3% | **>35%** | Architecture-aware reasoning + multi-step planning |
| **HumanEval** | Current best: ~95% | **>98%** | Tier 1 language specialization |
| **LiveCodeBench** | Varies | **Top 3** | Dynamic data contamination prevention |
| **Terminal-Bench** | Varies | **#1** | Agentic tool-use training |
| **Enterprise Security Score** | No standard exists | **Create the benchmark** | Saturday Security Benchmark (SSB) |

### 6.2 Saturday's Custom Evaluation Suite

> [!TIP]
> The models that define the benchmarks control the narrative. Saturday will introduce benchmarks that matter to *enterprises*, not just researchers.

#### Saturday Enterprise Benchmark (SEB)

| Test Category | What It Measures | # Test Cases |
|---|---|---|
| **Multi-File Coherence** | Can the model make consistent changes across 10+ files? | 200 |
| **Architecture Adherence** | Does generated code follow the project's established patterns? | 150 |
| **Security-by-Default** | What % of generated code passes OWASP Top 10 checks without fixes? | 300 |
| **Legacy Modernization** | Can it correctly migrate COBOL/mainframe patterns to modern code? | 100 |
| **Compliance Accuracy** | Does it generate GDPR/HIPAA/SOC2-compliant code by default? | 200 |
| **Long-Session Coherence** | After 100+ turns, does it still follow initial instructions? | 50 |
| **Incident Response** | Given prod error logs, can it diagnose and generate a correct fix? | 100 |
| **Test Generation Quality** | Do generated tests catch real bugs? (mutation testing) | 200 |

