## Summary: Why Saturday Wins

| Dimension | Claude Opus 4.6 | GPT Codex | **Saturday** |
|---|---|---|---|
| Context Understanding | Loses coherence after 50K tokens | Loses context mid-session | **1M token window + persistent project memory** |
| Security | ~48% vuln rate in suggestions | Hallucinated dependencies | **6-layer zero-trust validation, 0% known vulns** |
| Speed | Adaptive thinking adds latency | 20-30 min for simple tasks | **<200ms to <30s, intelligently routed** |
| Enterprise Features | None built-in | Limited API access | **Full SSO, RBAC, compliance, audit trails** |
| Pricing | Aggressive rate limiting | Single prompt eats weekly budget | **Unlimited enterprise tier, predictable pricing** |
| Legacy Support | Minimal | None | **COBOL migration, mainframe modernization** |
| CI/CD Integration | Bolt-on | Bolt-on | **Native CI/CD pipeline integration** |
| Reliability | API instability, deprecations | Concurrency bugs, undo failures | **Stable API contract, full state rollback** |
| Transparency | Black box | Silent model downgrades | **Full provenance tags, transparent routing** |

> [!NOTE]
> Saturday doesn't just beat the competition on benchmarks — it's the first coding model built **for enterprises, by enterprise standards**. Every feature, every architectural decision, every training data choice is optimized for MNC-grade production deployment.

